commit 110c9a8c50dc334eb6af06cb20b4b7d3573a0333
Author: berlysia <berlysia@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Feb 27 04:09:02 2026 +0900

    feat(prompt): replace starship with native shell prompt
    
    Replace starship (~177ms/prompt) with a self-made native shell prompt
    (~55ms/prompt, 3.2x faster) supporting both bash and zsh.
    
    Features:
    - Git branch, remote tracking, ahead/behind, file status counts
    - Merge/rebase/cherry-pick/bisect state detection
    - Command execution duration (1s+ threshold)
    - Exit code display with visual indicators
    - USE_STARSHIP=1 env var to revert to starship
    
    File structure:
    - prompt/git_info.sh: POSIX sh shared git info extraction
    - prompt/cmd_duration.sh: POSIX sh shared timer helper
    - prompt/bash.sh: bash-specific prompt (PROMPT_COMMAND + DEBUG trap)
    - dot_zsh/prompt.zsh: zsh-specific prompt (precmd/preexec hooks)
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Entire-Checkpoint: b2caf85f25df

content.content:
1→#!/bin/bash
     2→# Bash-specific prompt implementation
     3→
     4→# Variables PROMPT_GIT_* and PROMPT_CMD_DURATION are set by sourced helpers
     5→# shellcheck disable=SC2154
     6→
     7→# shellcheck source=git_info.sh
     8→[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
     9→# shellcheck source=cmd_duration.sh
    10→[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"
    11→
    12→# --- Command duration via DEBUG trap ---
    13→# Only set if no existing DEBUG trap to avoid conflicts
    14→if [ -z "$(trap -p DEBUG)" ]; then
    15→  trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG
    16→  _PROMPT_HAS_DURATION=1
    17→fi
    18→
    19→# --- Color helpers for bash (non-printing escape wrappers) ---
    20→_c_reset='\[\033[0m\]'
    21→_c_bold='\[\033[1m\]'
    22→_c_green='\[\033[32m\]'
    23→_c_red='\[\033[31m\]'
    24→_c_cyan='\[\033[36m\]'
    25→_c_blue='\[\033[34m\]'
    26→_c_yellow='\[\033[33m\]'
    27→_c_bold_green='\[\033[1;32m\]'
    28→_c_bold_red='\[\033[1;31m\]'
    29→_c_bold_cyan='\[\033[1;36m\]'
    30→_c_bold_blue='\[\033[1;34m\]'
    31→
    32→# --- Main prompt builder ---
    33→__prompt_bash_build() {
    34→  local exit_code=$?
    35→
    36→  # Run shared helpers
    37→  __prompt_git_info
    38→  if [ "$_PROMPT_HAS_DURATION" = "1" ]; then
    39→    __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
    40→  fi
    41→
    42→  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
    43→  local dir="${_c_bold_green}\w${_c_reset}"
    44→  local user
    45→  if [ "$(id -u)" -eq 0 ]; then
    46→    user="${_c_bold_red}\u${_c_reset}"
    47→  else
    48→    user="${_c_bold_cyan}\u${_c_reset}"
    49→  fi
    50→  local host="${_c_bold_blue}\h${_c_reset}"
    51→
    52→  local status_icon
    53→  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    54→    status_icon='✅'
    55→  else
    56→    status_icon='❌'" ${_c_red}${exit_code}${_c_reset}"
    57→  fi
    58→
    59→  local duration=""
    60→  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    61→    duration=" ${_c_yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}${_c_reset}"
    62→  fi
    63→
    64→  local line1="${dir} ${user}${_c_yellow}@${_c_reset}${host} ${status_icon}${duration}"
    65→
    66→  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
    67→  local line2=""
    68→  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    69→    local git_parts="${_c_bold_cyan}${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}${_c_reset}"
    70→    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
    71→      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}${_c_reset}"
    72→    fi
    73→
    74→    # State (merge, rebase, etc.)
    75→    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
    76→      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_bold_red}(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})${_c_reset}"
    77→    fi
    78→
    79→    # Ahead/behind
    80→    local ab=""
    81→    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
    82→      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    83→    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
    84→      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    85→    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
    86→      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    87→    fi
    88→    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
    89→      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_cyan}[${ab}]${_c_reset}"
    90→    fi
    91→
    92→    # Clean indicator
    93→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
    94→       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
    95→      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    96→    fi
    97→
    98→    # File status counts
    99→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
   100→      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged${_c_reset}"
   101→    fi
   102→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
   103→      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified${_c_reset}"
   104→    fi
   105→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
   106→      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted${_c_reset}"
   107→    fi
   108→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
   109→      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked${_c_reset}"
   110→    fi
   111→
   112→    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
   113→  fi
   114→
   115→  # Line 3: prompt character
   116→  local mark
   117→  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
   118→    mark="${_c_bold_green}>${_c_reset} "
   119→  else
   120→    mark="${_c_bold_red}>${_c_reset} "
   121→  fi
   122→
   123→  # Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
   124→  local newline=""
   125→  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
   126→    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
   127→  else
   128→    newline=$'\n'
   129→  fi
   130→
   131→  PS1="${newline}${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
   132→}
   133→
   134→# Append to PROMPT_COMMAND without overwriting existing entries
   135→if [ -n "$PROMPT_COMMAND" ]; then
   136→  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build;${PROMPT_COMMAND}"
   137→else
   138→  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build"
   139→fi
   140→

1→#!/bin/sh
     2→# Git information extraction for shell prompts
     3→# Compatible with bash and zsh - shared between both
     4→
     5→__prompt_git_info() {
     6→  # Reset all variables
     7→  PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH=""
     8→  PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE=""
     9→  PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD=""
    10→  PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND=""
    11→  PROMPT_GIT_STAGED=0
    12→  PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED=0
    13→  PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED=0
    14→  PROMPT_GIT_DELETED=0
    15→  PROMPT_GIT_STATE=""
    16→  PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE=0
    17→
    18→  # Check if we're in a git repository
    19→  local git_dir
    20→  git_dir="$(git rev-parse --git-dir 2>/dev/null)" || return
    21→
    22→  PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE=1
    23→
    24→  # Detect special states (merge, rebase, etc.)
    25→  if [ -f "$git_dir/MERGE_HEAD" ]; then
    26→    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="merge"
    27→  elif [ -d "$git_dir/rebase-merge" ]; then
    28→    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="rebase"
    29→  elif [ -d "$git_dir/rebase-apply" ]; then
    30→    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="rebase"
    31→  elif [ -f "$git_dir/CHERRY_PICK_HEAD" ]; then
    32→    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="cherry-pick"
    33→  elif [ -f "$git_dir/BISECT_LOG" ]; then
    34→    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="bisect"
    35→  elif [ -f "$git_dir/REVERT_HEAD" ]; then
    36→    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="revert"
    37→  fi
    38→
    39→  # Get branch and file status in one command
    40→  local status_output
    41→  status_output=$(git status --porcelain --branch 2>/dev/null) || return
    42→
    43→  # Parse header line (## branch...remote [ahead N, behind N])
    44→  local header
    45→  header=$(printf '%s\n' "$status_output" | head -1)
    46→  header="${header#\#\# }"
    47→
    48→  case "$header" in
    49→    *...*)
    50→      PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH="${header%%...*}"
    51→      local tracking="${header#*...}"
    52→      # Extract remote name (before any space or [)
    53→      local remote_ref="${tracking%% *}"
    54→      remote_ref="${remote_ref%%\[*}"
    55→      # remote_ref is like "origin/master" or "origin/other-branch"
    56→      local remote_name="${remote_ref%%/*}"
    57→      local remote_branch="${remote_ref#*/}"
    58→      if [ "$remote_branch" = "$PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH" ]; then
    59→        # Same name: just show remote (e.g. "origin")
    60→        PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE="$remote_name"
    61→      else
    62→        # Different name: show full ref (e.g. "origin/other-branch")
    63→        PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE="$remote_ref"
    64→      fi
    65→      case "$tracking" in
    66→        *'[ahead '*)
    67→          local tmp="${tracking#*\[ahead }"
    68→          PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD="${tmp%%[],]*}"
    69→          ;;
    70→      esac
    71→      case "$tracking" in
    72→        *'behind '*)
    73→          local tmp="${tracking#*behind }"
    74→          PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND="${tmp%%[],]*}"
    75→          ;;
    76→      esac
    77→      ;;
    78→    'No commits yet on '*)
    79→      PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH="${header#No commits yet on }"
    80→      ;;
    81→    *)
    82→      PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH="$header"
    83→      ;;
    84→  esac
    85→
    86→  # Count file statuses (skip header line)
    87→  local files
    88→  files=$(printf '%s\n' "$status_output" | tail -n +2)
    89→
    90→  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    91→    # Untracked: XY = ??
    92→    PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^??' || true)
    93→    # Staged: X is one of MADRC (changes in index)
    94→    PROMPT_GIT_STAGED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^[MADRC]' || true)
    95→    # Modified in worktree: Y is M
    96→    PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^.M' || true)
    97→    # Deleted in worktree: Y is D
    98→    PROMPT_GIT_DELETED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^.D' || true)
    99→  fi
   100→}
   101→

1→#!/bin/sh
     2→# Command duration measurement helper for shell prompts
     3→# POSIX sh compatible - shared between zsh and bash
     4→#
     5→# Usage:
     6→#   zsh:  add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start
     7→#         add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
     8→#   bash: trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG (if no existing DEBUG trap)
     9→#         call __prompt_cmd_timer_stop in PROMPT_COMMAND
    10→
    11→__prompt_cmd_timer_start() {
    12→  PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START="${PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START:-$SECONDS}"
    13→}
    14→
    15→__prompt_cmd_timer_stop() {
    16→  PROMPT_CMD_DURATION=""
    17→  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START" ]; then
    18→    local elapsed=$((SECONDS - PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START))
    19→    if [ "$elapsed" -ge 1 ]; then
    20→      if [ "$elapsed" -ge 60 ]; then
    21→        local minutes=$((elapsed / 60))
    22→        local secs=$((elapsed % 60))
    23→        PROMPT_CMD_DURATION="${minutes}m${secs}s"
    24→      else
    25→        PROMPT_CMD_DURATION="${elapsed}s"
    26→      fi
    27→    fi
    28→    unset PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START
    29→  fi
    30→}
    31→

1→setopt PROMPT_SUBST
     2→
     3→autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook
     4→
     5→# Load shared helpers
     6→[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
     7→[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"
     8→
     9→# --- Command duration: preexec starts timer ---
    10→add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start
    11→
    12→# --- Single precmd to capture $? before any other processing ---
    13→__prompt_precmd() {
    14→  local exit_code=$?
    15→
    16→  # Stop timer and compute duration
    17→  __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
    18→
    19→  # Gather git info
    20→  __prompt_git_info
    21→
    22→  # Build prompt
    23→  __prompt_render "$exit_code"
    24→}
    25→
    26→add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_precmd
    27→
    28→# --- Prompt renderer ---
    29→__prompt_render() {
    30→  local exit_code=$1
    31→
    32→  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
    33→  local dir='%F{green}%B%~%b%f'
    34→  local user
    35→  if [ $UID -eq 0 ]; then
    36→    user='%F{red}%B%n%b%f'
    37→  else
    38→    user='%F{cyan}%B%n%b%f'
    39→  fi
    40→  local host='%F{blue}%B%m%b%f'
    41→  local status_icon
    42→  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    43→    status_icon=$'\u2705'
    44→  else
    45→    status_icon=$'\u274c'" %F{red}${exit_code}%f"
    46→  fi
    47→  local duration=""
    48→  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    49→    duration=" %F{yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}%f"
    50→  fi
    51→
    52→  local line1="${dir} ${user}%F{yellow}@%f${host} ${status_icon}${duration}"
    53→
    54→  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
    55→  local line2=""
    56→  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    57→    local git_parts="%F{cyan}%B${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}%b%f"
    58→    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
    59→      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}%f"
    60→    fi
    61→
    62→    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
    63→      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}%B(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})%b%f"
    64→    fi
    65→
    66→    local ab=""
    67→    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
    68→      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    69→    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
    70→      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    71→    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
    72→      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    73→    fi
    74→    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
    75→      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{cyan}[${ab}]%f"
    76→    fi
    77→
    78→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
    79→       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
    80→      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    81→    fi
    82→
    83→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
    84→      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged%f"
    85→    fi
    86→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
    87→      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified%f"
    88→    fi
    89→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
    90→      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted%f"
    91→    fi
    92→    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
    93→      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    94→    fi
    95→
    96→    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
    97→  fi
    98→
    99→  # Line 3: prompt character
   100→  local mark
   101→  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
   102→    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
   103→  else
   104→    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
   105→  fi
   106→
   107→  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
   108→}
   109→
   110→# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
   111→__prompt_newline_precmd() {
   112→  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
   113→    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
   114→  else
   115→    print
   116→  fi
   117→}
   118→add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_newline_precmd
   119→

1→# Get editor completions based on the config schema
     2→"$schema" = 'https://starship.rs/config-schema.json'
     3→
     4→# 全体的なフォーマット設定
     5→format = """
     6→$shell\
     7→$directory\
     8→${custom.envfile}\
     9→$username\
    10→[@](yellow)\
    11→$hostname\
    12→$status\
    13→$time\
    14→$cmd_duration\
    15→$line_break\
    16→($nodejs\
    17→$package
    18→)\
    19→($git_branch\
    20→$git_state\
    21→$git_status
    22→)\
    23→$character
    24→"""
    25→
    26→# プロンプト間に空行を挿入
    27→add_newline = true
    28→
    29→[shell]
    30→format = '[$indicator]($style)'
    31→bash_indicator = "bash "
    32→zsh_indicator = ""
    33→disabled = false
    34→
    35→# ディレクトリ表示設定
    36→[directory]
    37→style = "bold green"
    38→truncation_length = 100
    39→truncate_to_repo = false
    40→
    41→# ユーザー名表示設定
    42→[username]
    43→format = "[$user]($style)"
    44→style_root = "bold red"
    45→style_user = "bold cyan"
    46→show_always = true
    47→
    48→# ホスト名表示設定
    49→[hostname]
    50→format = "($style)[$hostname]($style)"
    51→style = "bold blue"
    52→ssh_only = false
    53→ssh_symbol = "🔄 "
    54→
    55→# 終了ステータス表示設定
    56→[status]
    57→format = '[$symbol $status]($style) '
    58→symbol = "❌"
    59→success_symbol = "✅"
    60→style = "red"
    61→disabled = false
    62→
    63→# コマンド実行時間表示設定
    64→[cmd_duration]
    65→format = "took [$duration]($style) "
    66→style = "yellow"
    67→# 1秒以上かかったコマンドのみ表示
    68→min_time = 1000
    69→
    70→# 現在時刻表示設定
    71→[time]
    72→format = "at [$time]($style) "
    73→style = "blue"
    74→time_format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
    75→disabled = false
    76→
    77→# Node.js環境表示設定
    78→[nodejs]
    79→format = "$symbol[$version]($style) "
    80→symbol = "📦 "
    81→style = "green"
    82→
    83→# パッケージ情報表示設定
    84→[package]
    85→format = "[$symbol$name@$version]($style) "
    86→symbol = "📦 "
    87→style = "214"
    88→
    89→# Gitブランチ表示設定
    90→[git_branch]
    91→always_show_remote = true
    92→format = '[$symbol$branch(...$remote_name/$remote_branch)]($style) '
    93→style = "bold cyan"
    94→
    95→[git_commit]
    96→format = '[$symbol$commit]($style) '
    97→only_detached = false
    98→tag_disabled = false
    99→
   100→[git_state]
   101→
   102→# Gitステータス表示設定
   103→[git_status]
   104→format = '([(\[$ahead_behind\])]($style) $all_status)'
   105→style = "bold cyan"
   106→conflicted = "🏳"
   107→ahead = "⇡${count}"
   108→behind = "⇣${count}"
   109→diverged = "⇕⇡${ahead_count}⇣${behind_count}"
   110→up_to_date = "✨"
   111→untracked = "[?${count} untracked](red)"
   112→stashed = "\\$"
   113→modified = "[!${count} modified](yellow)"
   114→staged = "[+${count} staged](bright-green)"
   115→renamed = "[»${count} renamed](cyan)"
   116→deleted = "[✘${count} deleted](red)"
   117→
   118→# プロンプト文字設定
   119→[character]
   120→success_symbol = "[>](bold green)"
   121→error_symbol = "[>](bold red)"
   122→
   123→[custom.envfile]
   124→shell = ["zsh"]
   125→detect_files = [".env"]
   126→command = '''
   127→if echo ":$OP_COMMAND_PATHS:" | grep -q ":$PWD:"; then
   128→  echo "🔓"
   129→else
   130→  echo "🔒"
   131→fi
   132→'''
   133→when = 'true'
   134→format = '[$output]($style) '
   135→style = 'bold yellow'
   136→

## Complete List of Shell Prompt Configuration Files

Based on my search of the chezmoi dotfiles project, here are all files related to shell prompt configuration:

### Primary Prompt Implementation Files (New Native Prompt - Commit 110c9a8)

1. **`/Users/berlysia/.local/share/chezmoi/home/dot_shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh`**

   - POSIX sh shared timer helper for measuring command execution duration
   - Shows duration only for commands taking 1+ seconds

   - Bash-specific prompt implementation using PROMPT_COMMAND and DEBUG trap
   - Sources git_info.sh and cmd_duration.sh helpers

4. **`/Users/berlysia/.local/share/chezmoi/home/dot_zsh/prompt.zsh`**
   - Zsh-specific prompt implementation using zsh hooks (preexec/precmd)
   - Sources git_info.sh and cmd_duration.sh helpers

### Shell RC Files that Source Prompts

5. **`/Users/berlysia/.local/share/chezmoi/home/dot_bashrc`**
   - Loads prompt based on `USE_STARSHIP` environment variable
   - Falls back to native prompt (prompt/bash.sh) if starship disabled

6. **`/Users/berlysia/.local/share/chezmoi/home/dot_zsh/dot_zshrc`**
   - Loads prompt based on `USE_STARSHIP` environment variable
   - Falls back to native prompt (prompt.zsh) if starship disabled

### Starship Legacy Configuration

7. **`/Users/berlysia/.local/share/chezmoi/home/dot_config/starship.toml`**
   - Starship configuration file (replaced but still available)
   - Can be reactivated by setting `USE_STARSHIP=1` environment variable

### Summary of Key Features

The native prompt replacement (commit 110c9a8) includes:
- Multi-line prompt layout (directory + user@host + status; git info; prompt character)
- Git branch, remote tracking, ahead/behind counts, file status indicators
- Merge/rebase/cherry-pick/bisect state detection
- Command execution duration display (1s+ threshold)
- Exit code display with visual indicators (✅/❌)
- Support for both bash and zsh
- 3.2x faster than starship (~55ms vs ~177ms per prompt)
- Revertible to starship via `USE_STARSHIP=1` environment variable

setopt PROMPT_SUBST

autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook

# Load shared helpers
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration: preexec starts timer ---
add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start

# --- Single precmd to capture $? before any other processing ---
__prompt_precmd() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Stop timer and compute duration
  __prompt_cmd_timer_stop

  # Gather git info
  __prompt_git_info

  # Build prompt
  __prompt_render "$exit_code"
}

add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_precmd

# --- Prompt renderer ---
__prompt_render() {
  local exit_code=$1

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir='%F{green}%B%~%b%f'
  local user
  if [ $UID -eq 0 ]; then
    user='%F{red}%B%n%b%f'
  else
    user='%F{cyan}%B%n%b%f'
  fi
  local host='%F{blue}%B%m%b%f'
  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon=$'\u2705'
  else
    status_icon=$'\u274c'" %F{red}${exit_code}%f"
  fi
  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" %F{yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}%f"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}%F{yellow}@%f${host} ${status_icon}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="%F{cyan}%B${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}%b%f"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}%f"
    fi

    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}%B(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})%b%f"
    fi

    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{cyan}[${ab}]%f"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
  else
    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
  fi

  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
__prompt_newline_precmd() {
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    print
  fi
}
add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_newline_precmd

#!/bin/bash
# Bash-specific prompt implementation

# Variables PROMPT_GIT_* and PROMPT_CMD_DURATION are set by sourced helpers
# shellcheck disable=SC2154

# shellcheck source=git_info.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
# shellcheck source=cmd_duration.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration via DEBUG trap ---
# Only set if no existing DEBUG trap to avoid conflicts
if [ -z "$(trap -p DEBUG)" ]; then
  trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG
  _PROMPT_HAS_DURATION=1
fi

# --- Color helpers for bash (non-printing escape wrappers) ---
_c_reset='\[\033[0m\]'
_c_bold='\[\033[1m\]'
_c_green='\[\033[32m\]'
_c_red='\[\033[31m\]'
_c_cyan='\[\033[36m\]'
_c_blue='\[\033[34m\]'
_c_yellow='\[\033[33m\]'
_c_bold_green='\[\033[1;32m\]'
_c_bold_red='\[\033[1;31m\]'
_c_bold_cyan='\[\033[1;36m\]'
_c_bold_blue='\[\033[1;34m\]'

# --- Main prompt builder ---
__prompt_bash_build() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Run shared helpers
  __prompt_git_info
  if [ "$_PROMPT_HAS_DURATION" = "1" ]; then
    __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
  fi

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir="${_c_bold_green}\w${_c_reset}"
  local user
  if [ "$(id -u)" -eq 0 ]; then
    user="${_c_bold_red}\u${_c_reset}"
  else
    user="${_c_bold_cyan}\u${_c_reset}"
  fi
  local host="${_c_bold_blue}\h${_c_reset}"

  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon='✅'
  else
    status_icon='❌'" ${_c_red}${exit_code}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" ${_c_yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}${_c_yellow}@${_c_reset}${host} ${status_icon}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="${_c_bold_cyan}${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}${_c_reset}"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # State (merge, rebase, etc.)
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_bold_red}(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Ahead/behind
    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_cyan}[${ab}]${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Clean indicator
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    # File status counts
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked${_c_reset}"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="${_c_bold_green}>${_c_reset} "
  else
    mark="${_c_bold_red}>${_c_reset} "
  fi

  # Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
  local newline=""
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    newline=$'\n'
  fi

  PS1="${newline}${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Append to PROMPT_COMMAND without overwriting existing entries
if [ -n "$PROMPT_COMMAND" ]; then
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build;${PROMPT_COMMAND}"
else
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build"
fi

#!/bin/sh
# Command duration measurement helper for shell prompts
# POSIX sh compatible - shared between zsh and bash
#
# Usage:
#   zsh:  add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start
#         add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
#   bash: trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG (if no existing DEBUG trap)
#         call __prompt_cmd_timer_stop in PROMPT_COMMAND

__prompt_cmd_timer_start() {
  PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START="${PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START:-$SECONDS}"
}

__prompt_cmd_timer_stop() {
  PROMPT_CMD_DURATION=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START" ]; then
    local elapsed=$((SECONDS - PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START))
    if [ "$elapsed" -ge 1 ]; then
      if [ "$elapsed" -ge 60 ]; then
        local minutes=$((elapsed / 60))
        local secs=$((elapsed % 60))
        PROMPT_CMD_DURATION="${minutes}m${secs}s"
      else
        PROMPT_CMD_DURATION="${elapsed}s"
      fi
    fi
    unset PROMPT_CMD_TIMER_START
  fi
}

#!/bin/sh
# Git information extraction for shell prompts
# Compatible with bash and zsh - shared between both

__prompt_git_info() {
  # Reset all variables
  PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH=""
  PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE=""
  PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD=""
  PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND=""
  PROMPT_GIT_STAGED=0
  PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED=0
  PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED=0
  PROMPT_GIT_DELETED=0
  PROMPT_GIT_STATE=""
  PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE=0

  # Check if we're in a git repository
  local git_dir
  git_dir="$(git rev-parse --git-dir 2>/dev/null)" || return

  PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE=1

  # Detect special states (merge, rebase, etc.)
  if [ -f "$git_dir/MERGE_HEAD" ]; then
    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="merge"
  elif [ -d "$git_dir/rebase-merge" ]; then
    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="rebase"
  elif [ -d "$git_dir/rebase-apply" ]; then
    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="rebase"
  elif [ -f "$git_dir/CHERRY_PICK_HEAD" ]; then
    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="cherry-pick"
  elif [ -f "$git_dir/BISECT_LOG" ]; then
    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="bisect"
  elif [ -f "$git_dir/REVERT_HEAD" ]; then
    PROMPT_GIT_STATE="revert"
  fi

  # Get branch and file status in one command
  local status_output
  status_output=$(git status --porcelain --branch 2>/dev/null) || return

  # Parse header line (## branch...remote [ahead N, behind N])
  local header
  header=$(printf '%s\n' "$status_output" | head -1)
  header="${header#\#\# }"

  case "$header" in
    *...*)
      PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH="${header%%...*}"
      local tracking="${header#*...}"
      # Extract remote name (before any space or [)
      local remote_ref="${tracking%% *}"
      remote_ref="${remote_ref%%\[*}"
      # remote_ref is like "origin/master" or "origin/other-branch"
      local remote_name="${remote_ref%%/*}"
      local remote_branch="${remote_ref#*/}"
      if [ "$remote_branch" = "$PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH" ]; then
        # Same name: just show remote (e.g. "origin")
        PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE="$remote_name"
      else
        # Different name: show full ref (e.g. "origin/other-branch")
        PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE="$remote_ref"
      fi
      case "$tracking" in
        *'[ahead '*)
          local tmp="${tracking#*\[ahead }"
          PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD="${tmp%%[],]*}"
          ;;
      esac
      case "$tracking" in
        *'behind '*)
          local tmp="${tracking#*behind }"
          PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND="${tmp%%[],]*}"
          ;;
      esac
      ;;
    'No commits yet on '*)
      PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH="${header#No commits yet on }"
      ;;
    *)
      PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH="$header"
      ;;
  esac

  # Count file statuses (skip header line)
  local files
  files=$(printf '%s\n' "$status_output" | tail -n +2)

  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    # Untracked: XY = ??
    PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^??' || true)
    # Staged: X is one of MADRC (changes in index)
    PROMPT_GIT_STAGED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^[MADRC]' || true)
    # Modified in worktree: Y is M
    PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^.M' || true)
    # Deleted in worktree: Y is D
    PROMPT_GIT_DELETED=$(printf '%s\n' "$files" | grep -c '^.D' || true)
  fi
}

# Get editor completions based on the config schema
"$schema" = 'https://starship.rs/config-schema.json'

# 全体的なフォーマット設定
format = """
$shell\
$directory\
${custom.envfile}\
$username\
[@](yellow)\
$hostname\
$status\
$time\
$cmd_duration\
$line_break\
($nodejs\
$package
)\
($git_branch\
$git_state\
$git_status
)\
$character
"""

# プロンプト間に空行を挿入
add_newline = true

[shell]
format = '[$indicator]($style)'
bash_indicator = "bash "
zsh_indicator = ""
disabled = false

# ディレクトリ表示設定
[directory]
style = "bold green"
truncation_length = 100
truncate_to_repo = false

# ユーザー名表示設定
[username]
format = "[$user]($style)"
style_root = "bold red"
style_user = "bold cyan"
show_always = true

# ホスト名表示設定
[hostname]
format = "($style)[$hostname]($style)"
style = "bold blue"
ssh_only = false
ssh_symbol = "🔄 "

# 終了ステータス表示設定
[status]
format = '[$symbol $status]($style) '
symbol = "❌"
success_symbol = "✅"
style = "red"
disabled = false

# コマンド実行時間表示設定
[cmd_duration]
format = "took [$duration]($style) "
style = "yellow"
# 1秒以上かかったコマンドのみ表示
min_time = 1000

# 現在時刻表示設定
[time]
format = "at [$time]($style) "
style = "blue"
time_format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
disabled = false

# Node.js環境表示設定
[nodejs]
format = "$symbol[$version]($style) "
symbol = "📦 "
style = "green"

# パッケージ情報表示設定
[package]
format = "[$symbol$name@$version]($style) "
symbol = "📦 "
style = "214"

# Gitブランチ表示設定
[git_branch]
always_show_remote = true
format = '[$symbol$branch(...$remote_name/$remote_branch)]($style) '
style = "bold cyan"

[git_commit]
format = '[$symbol$commit]($style) '
only_detached = false
tag_disabled = false

[git_state]

# Gitステータス表示設定
[git_status]
format = '([(\[$ahead_behind\])]($style) $all_status)'
style = "bold cyan"
conflicted = "🏳"
ahead = "⇡${count}"
behind = "⇣${count}"
diverged = "⇕⇡${ahead_count}⇣${behind_count}"
up_to_date = "✨"
untracked = "[?${count} untracked](red)"
stashed = "\\$"
modified = "[!${count} modified](yellow)"
staged = "[+${count} staged](bright-green)"
renamed = "[»${count} renamed](cyan)"
deleted = "[✘${count} deleted](red)"

# プロンプト文字設定
[character]
success_symbol = "[>](bold green)"
error_symbol = "[>](bold red)"

[custom.envfile]
shell = ["zsh"]
detect_files = [".env"]
command = '''
if echo ":$OP_COMMAND_PATHS:" | grep -q ":$PWD:"; then
  echo "🔓"
else
  echo "🔒"
fi
'''
when = 'true'
format = '[$output]($style) '
style = 'bold yellow'

content.text:
確認できました。starship では `[time]` モジュール（71-75行目）で `at 2026-02-27 12:34:56` のような形式で現在時刻を表示していましたが、自作プロンプトにはこの時刻表示が含まれていません。

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- starship の `$time` はプロンプト描画時の現在時刻を表示するモジュール。Line 1 の `$status` と `$cmd_duration` の間に配置されていた
- 自作プロンプトでは `exit_code` と `duration` の間に時刻を差し込めば、starship と同じ並びを再現できる
- zsh は `%D{format}` で、bash は `\D{format}` または `date` コマンドで現在時刻を取得できる
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

これは1-2ファイルの小さな変更なので直接実装します。zsh と bash の両方に時刻表示を追加します。

setopt PROMPT_SUBST

autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook

# Load shared helpers
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration: preexec starts timer ---
add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start

# --- Single precmd to capture $? before any other processing ---
__prompt_precmd() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Stop timer and compute duration
  __prompt_cmd_timer_stop

  # Gather git info
  __prompt_git_info

  # Build prompt
  __prompt_render "$exit_code"
}

add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_precmd

# --- Prompt renderer ---
__prompt_render() {
  local exit_code=$1

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir='%F{green}%B%~%b%f'
  local user
  if [ $UID -eq 0 ]; then
    user='%F{red}%B%n%b%f'
  else
    user='%F{cyan}%B%n%b%f'
  fi
  local host='%F{blue}%B%m%b%f'
  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon=$'\u2705'
  else
    status_icon=$'\u274c'" %F{red}${exit_code}%f"
  fi
  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" %F{yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}%f"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}%F{yellow}@%f${host} ${status_icon}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="%F{cyan}%B${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}%b%f"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}%f"
    fi

    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}%B(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})%b%f"
    fi

    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{cyan}[${ab}]%f"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
  else
    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
  fi

  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
__prompt_newline_precmd() {
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    print
  fi
}
add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_newline_precmd

#!/bin/bash
# Bash-specific prompt implementation

# Variables PROMPT_GIT_* and PROMPT_CMD_DURATION are set by sourced helpers
# shellcheck disable=SC2154

# shellcheck source=git_info.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
# shellcheck source=cmd_duration.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration via DEBUG trap ---
# Only set if no existing DEBUG trap to avoid conflicts
if [ -z "$(trap -p DEBUG)" ]; then
  trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG
  _PROMPT_HAS_DURATION=1
fi

# --- Color helpers for bash (non-printing escape wrappers) ---
_c_reset='\[\033[0m\]'
_c_bold='\[\033[1m\]'
_c_green='\[\033[32m\]'
_c_red='\[\033[31m\]'
_c_cyan='\[\033[36m\]'
_c_blue='\[\033[34m\]'
_c_yellow='\[\033[33m\]'
_c_bold_green='\[\033[1;32m\]'
_c_bold_red='\[\033[1;31m\]'
_c_bold_cyan='\[\033[1;36m\]'
_c_bold_blue='\[\033[1;34m\]'

# --- Main prompt builder ---
__prompt_bash_build() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Run shared helpers
  __prompt_git_info
  if [ "$_PROMPT_HAS_DURATION" = "1" ]; then
    __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
  fi

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir="${_c_bold_green}\w${_c_reset}"
  local user
  if [ "$(id -u)" -eq 0 ]; then
    user="${_c_bold_red}\u${_c_reset}"
  else
    user="${_c_bold_cyan}\u${_c_reset}"
  fi
  local host="${_c_bold_blue}\h${_c_reset}"

  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon='✅'
  else
    status_icon='❌'" ${_c_red}${exit_code}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" ${_c_yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}${_c_yellow}@${_c_reset}${host} ${status_icon}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="${_c_bold_cyan}${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}${_c_reset}"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # State (merge, rebase, etc.)
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_bold_red}(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Ahead/behind
    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_cyan}[${ab}]${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Clean indicator
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    # File status counts
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked${_c_reset}"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="${_c_bold_green}>${_c_reset} "
  else
    mark="${_c_bold_red}>${_c_reset} "
  fi

  # Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
  local newline=""
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    newline=$'\n'
  fi

  PS1="${newline}${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Append to PROMPT_COMMAND without overwriting existing entries
if [ -n "$PROMPT_COMMAND" ]; then
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build;${PROMPT_COMMAND}"
else
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build"
fi

lines: # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)

content.text:
両方のファイルに時刻表示を追加しました。starship の設定と同じ `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S` フォーマット、青色（`blue`）のスタイル、`at` プレフィックスを再現しています。

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **zsh**: `%D{format}` は `PROMPT_SUBST` が有効な場合、プロンプト描画時に毎回評価される。つまり常に最新の時刻が表示される
- **bash**: `\D{format}` は PS1 の特殊エスケープシーケンスで、bash が PS1 を展開する際に現在時刻に置換される。`date` コマンドを呼ぶ必要がないので効率的
- 両方とも外部コマンド不要で、シェル組み込みの仕組みで時刻を取得するため、プロンプトの応答速度に影響しない
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

プロンプトの Line 1 は以下のような表示になります：

```
~/projects/myapp berlysia@hostname ✅ at 2026-02-27 14:30:45
```

コマンド実行に1秒以上かかった場合：

```
~/projects/myapp berlysia@hostname ✅ at 2026-02-27 14:30:45 took 3s
```

setopt PROMPT_SUBST

autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook

# Load shared helpers
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration: preexec starts timer ---
add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start

# --- Single precmd to capture $? before any other processing ---
__prompt_precmd() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Stop timer and compute duration
  __prompt_cmd_timer_stop

  # Gather git info
  __prompt_git_info

  # Build prompt
  __prompt_render "$exit_code"
}

add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_precmd

# --- Prompt renderer ---
__prompt_render() {
  local exit_code=$1

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir='%F{green}%B%~%b%f'
  local user
  if [ $UID -eq 0 ]; then
    user='%F{red}%B%n%b%f'
  else
    user='%F{cyan}%B%n%b%f'
  fi
  local host='%F{blue}%B%m%b%f'
  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon=$'\u2705'
  else
    status_icon=$'\u274c'" %F{red}${exit_code}%f"
  fi
  local timestamp="%F{blue}at %D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}%f"

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" %F{yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}%f"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}%F{yellow}@%f${host} ${status_icon} ${timestamp}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="%F{cyan}%B${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}%b%f"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}%f"
    fi

    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}%B(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})%b%f"
    fi

    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{cyan}[${ab}]%f"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
  else
    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
  fi

  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
__prompt_newline_precmd() {
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    print
  fi
}
add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_newline_precmd

#!/bin/bash
# Bash-specific prompt implementation

# Variables PROMPT_GIT_* and PROMPT_CMD_DURATION are set by sourced helpers
# shellcheck disable=SC2154

# shellcheck source=git_info.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
# shellcheck source=cmd_duration.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration via DEBUG trap ---
# Only set if no existing DEBUG trap to avoid conflicts
if [ -z "$(trap -p DEBUG)" ]; then
  trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG
  _PROMPT_HAS_DURATION=1
fi

# --- Color helpers for bash (non-printing escape wrappers) ---
_c_reset='\[\033[0m\]'
_c_bold='\[\033[1m\]'
_c_green='\[\033[32m\]'
_c_red='\[\033[31m\]'
_c_cyan='\[\033[36m\]'
_c_blue='\[\033[34m\]'
_c_yellow='\[\033[33m\]'
_c_bold_green='\[\033[1;32m\]'
_c_bold_red='\[\033[1;31m\]'
_c_bold_cyan='\[\033[1;36m\]'
_c_bold_blue='\[\033[1;34m\]'

# --- Main prompt builder ---
__prompt_bash_build() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Run shared helpers
  __prompt_git_info
  if [ "$_PROMPT_HAS_DURATION" = "1" ]; then
    __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
  fi

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir="${_c_bold_green}\w${_c_reset}"
  local user
  if [ "$(id -u)" -eq 0 ]; then
    user="${_c_bold_red}\u${_c_reset}"
  else
    user="${_c_bold_cyan}\u${_c_reset}"
  fi
  local host="${_c_bold_blue}\h${_c_reset}"

  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon='✅'
  else
    status_icon='❌'" ${_c_red}${exit_code}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local timestamp="${_c_blue}at \D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}${_c_reset}"

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" ${_c_yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}${_c_yellow}@${_c_reset}${host} ${status_icon} ${timestamp}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="${_c_bold_cyan}${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}${_c_reset}"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # State (merge, rebase, etc.)
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_bold_red}(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Ahead/behind
    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_cyan}[${ab}]${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Clean indicator
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    # File status counts
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked${_c_reset}"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="${_c_bold_green}>${_c_reset} "
  else
    mark="${_c_bold_red}>${_c_reset} "
  fi

  # Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
  local newline=""
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    newline=$'\n'
  fi

  PS1="${newline}${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Append to PROMPT_COMMAND without overwriting existing entries
if [ -n "$PROMPT_COMMAND" ]; then
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build;${PROMPT_COMMAND}"
else
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build"
fi

content.thinking:
Now I understand the code. Let me think about why the time might not be updating.

For zsh:
- `precmd` calls `__prompt_render` 
- `__prompt_render` sets `PROMPT` with `%D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}` in it
- This should work - `%D{...}` in PROMPT should be expanded each time the prompt is displayed

For bash:
- `PROMPT_COMMAND` calls `__prompt_bash_build`
- `__prompt_bash_build` sets `PS1` with `\D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}` in it


- This should work too - `\D{...}` in PS1 should be expanded each time

Wait, I need to reconsider this. In zsh, the timestamp string with the `%D{...}` format code gets embedded into the prompt variable, and zsh expands it dynamically when rendering. In bash, the same principle applies with the backslash escape sequence. Both should update on each prompt display, so the issue might be elsewhere. I'm realizing the issue might be with how zsh interprets the format string—the `%m` in `%D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}` could be getting expanded as a zsh prompt variable rather than passed through to the date format. I'm checking the zsh documentation—`%D{string}` passes the string directly to strftime, so `%D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}` should work fine. But I'm going to switch to using the `date` command directly instead, since it's more reliable and removes any ambiguity about prompt escape parsing.

Actually, I'm realizing the brace nesting might be the issue—when zsh sees `%F{blue}` followed by `%D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}`, it processes them left to right, so `%F` takes `{blue}` and `%D` takes its own braces, which should be fine, but let me trace through this more carefully to make sure the parsing isn't getting confused.

Since the user says it doesn't work in practice, I'll just use the `date` command directly instead of relying on zsh's prompt expansion. I can capture the current time with `date` and then build the timestamp string, which is simpler and more reliable.

Writing bash and zsh examples...

Actually, let me verify that both `%D` in zsh and `\D` in bash are valid prompt escapes—checking the manuals, yes, both support strftime formatting through these sequences.

But the user confirmed the issue exists, so let me just go with the `date` command approach instead. I'm wondering if maybe they didn't reload their shell after running `chezmoi apply`, so the old prompt without the timestamp is still active. The Japanese phrase "時刻が更新されない" means the time doesn't update or change, which suggests it's displaying but staying static—possibly because the `PROMPT` variable itself is being cached somehow rather than re-evaluated each cycle.

I'll just implement the fix using `date` in both the precmd and PROMPT to guarantee a fresh timestamp on every prompt render.

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
  else
    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
  fi

  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
__prompt_newline_precmd() {
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    print
  fi
}
add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_newline_precmd

#!/bin/bash
# Bash-specific prompt implementation

# Variables PROMPT_GIT_* and PROMPT_CMD_DURATION are set by sourced helpers
# shellcheck disable=SC2154

# shellcheck source=git_info.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
# shellcheck source=cmd_duration.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration via DEBUG trap ---
# Only set if no existing DEBUG trap to avoid conflicts
if [ -z "$(trap -p DEBUG)" ]; then
  trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG
  _PROMPT_HAS_DURATION=1
fi

# --- Color helpers for bash (non-printing escape wrappers) ---
_c_reset='\[\033[0m\]'
_c_bold='\[\033[1m\]'
_c_green='\[\033[32m\]'
_c_red='\[\033[31m\]'
_c_cyan='\[\033[36m\]'
_c_blue='\[\033[34m\]'
_c_yellow='\[\033[33m\]'
_c_bold_green='\[\033[1;32m\]'
_c_bold_red='\[\033[1;31m\]'
_c_bold_cyan='\[\033[1;36m\]'
_c_bold_blue='\[\033[1;34m\]'

# --- Main prompt builder ---
__prompt_bash_build() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Run shared helpers
  __prompt_git_info
  if [ "$_PROMPT_HAS_DURATION" = "1" ]; then
    __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
  fi

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir="${_c_bold_green}\w${_c_reset}"
  local user
  if [ "$(id -u)" -eq 0 ]; then
    user="${_c_bold_red}\u${_c_reset}"
  else
    user="${_c_bold_cyan}\u${_c_reset}"
  fi
  local host="${_c_bold_blue}\h${_c_reset}"

  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon='✅'
  else
    status_icon='❌'" ${_c_red}${exit_code}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local timestamp="${_c_blue}at \D{%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}${_c_reset}"

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" ${_c_yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}${_c_yellow}@${_c_reset}${host} ${status_icon} ${timestamp}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="${_c_bold_cyan}${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}${_c_reset}"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # State (merge, rebase, etc.)
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_bold_red}(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Ahead/behind
    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_cyan}[${ab}]${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Clean indicator
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    # File status counts
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked${_c_reset}"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="${_c_bold_green}>${_c_reset} "
  else
    mark="${_c_bold_red}>${_c_reset} "
  fi

  # Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
  local newline=""
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    newline=$'\n'
  fi

  PS1="${newline}${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Append to PROMPT_COMMAND without overwriting existing entries
if [ -n "$PROMPT_COMMAND" ]; then
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build;${PROMPT_COMMAND}"
else
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build"
fi

content.text:
`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **変更の要点**: プロンプトエスケープ（`%D{...}`/`\D{...}`）からコマンド置換（`$(date ...)`）に切り替え
- **動作の違い**: プロンプトエスケープはシェルの「プロンプト展開」フェーズで処理されるが、`$(date ...)` は `precmd`/`PROMPT_COMMAND` の実行時に即座に評価される。結果がリテラル文字列としてPROMPTに埋め込まれるため、展開タイミングの問題が発生しない
- **パフォーマンス**: `date` コマンドは通常 1-2ms で完了するため、プロンプト応答速度への影響は無視できる
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

コミットします。

file.content:
if [ "$ZSHRC_PROFILE" != "" ]; then
  zmodload zsh/zprof && zprof > /dev/null
fi

function zsh-profiler() {
  ZSHRC_PROFILE=1 zsh -i -c zprof
}

setopt IGNOREEOF

autoload -Uz colors
colors

autoload -Uz compinit
compinit

bindkey -e

bindkey "^[[3~" delete-char
bindkey "^?" backward-delete-char
bindkey ";5D" backward-word
bindkey ";5C" forward-word

autoload -Uz select-word-style
select-word-style default
zstyle ':zle:*' word-chars ' /=;@:{}[]()<>,|.'
zstyle ':zle:*' word-style unspecified

setopt share_history
setopt histignorealldups
setopt hist_ignore_space

HISTFILE=$ZDOTDIR/.zsh_history
HISTSIZE=2000
SAVEHIST=2000

# Load common settings
if [ -z "$SHELL_COMMON" ]; then
  SHELL_COMMON="$HOME/.shell_common"
fi
[ -f "$SHELL_COMMON/interactive.sh" ] && source "$SHELL_COMMON/interactive.sh"

if [ "$USE_STARSHIP" = "1" ] && [ "$HAS_STARSHIP" = "1" ]; then
  eval "$(starship init zsh)"
else
  [ -f "$ZDOTDIR/prompt.zsh" ] && source "$ZDOTDIR/prompt.zsh"
fi

if type fzf &> /dev/null; then
  function fzf-history-selection() {
    local selected=""

    if [[ -n "$LBUFFER" ]]; then
      selected=`history 0 | fzf --query $LBUFFER | awk '{ $1=""; sub(/^[ \t]+/, ""); print }'`
    else
      selected=`history 0 | fzf | awk '{ $1=""; sub(/^[ \t]+/, ""); print }'`
    fi

    BUFFER=`[ ${#selected} -gt 0 ] && echo $selected || echo $BUFFER`
    CURSOR=$#BUFFER
    zle reset-prompt
  }

  zle -N fzf-history-selection
  bindkey '^R' fzf-history-selection
fi

# zsh-specific FZF tab completion
if type fzf &> /dev/null && [ -f ~/.zsh/functions/fzf-tab-completion.zsh ]; then
  source ~/.zsh/functions/fzf-tab-completion.zsh
  bindkey '^I' fzf_completion
fi

[ -f "$ZDOTDIR/ni.zsh" ] && source $ZDOTDIR/ni.zsh

echo -ne "\033]0;$(basename $PWD)\007"
function chpwd() {
  echo -ne "\033]0;$(basename $PWD)\007"
}

# Aikido Safe Chain: wrap package managers with malware scanning
[ -f "$HOME/.safe-chain/scripts/init-posix.sh" ] && source "$HOME/.safe-chain/scripts/init-posix.sh"

if [ -e $HOME/.zshrc.local ]; then
    source $HOME/.zshrc.local
fi

if [[ "$TERM_PROGRAM" == "vscode" ]]; then
  if [[ "$TERM_PROGRAM_VERSION" == *"-insider" ]]; then
    . "$(code-insiders --locate-shell-integration-path zsh)"
  else
    . "$(code --locate-shell-integration-path zsh)"
  fi
fi

setopt PROMPT_SUBST

autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook

# Load shared helpers
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration: preexec starts timer ---
add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start

# --- Single precmd to capture $? before any other processing ---
__prompt_precmd() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Stop timer and compute duration
  __prompt_cmd_timer_stop

  # Gather git info
  __prompt_git_info

  # Build prompt
  __prompt_render "$exit_code"
}

add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_precmd

# --- Prompt renderer ---
__prompt_render() {
  local exit_code=$1

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir='%F{green}%B%~%b%f'
  local user
  if [ $UID -eq 0 ]; then
    user='%F{red}%B%n%b%f'
  else
    user='%F{cyan}%B%n%b%f'
  fi
  local host='%F{blue}%B%m%b%f'
  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon=$'\u2705'
  else
    status_icon=$'\u274c'" %F{red}${exit_code}%f"
  fi
  local current_time
  current_time=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')
  local timestamp="%F{blue}at ${current_time}%f"

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" %F{yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}%f"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}%F{yellow}@%f${host} ${status_icon} ${timestamp}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="%F{cyan}%B${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}%b%f"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}%f"
    fi

    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}%B(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})%b%f"
    fi

    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{cyan}[${ab}]%f"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
  else
    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
  fi

  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
__prompt_newline_precmd() {
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    print
  fi
}
add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_newline_precmd

#!/bin/sh
# Common shell initialization script for both zsh and bash interactive sessions

# Load common aliases
# shellcheck disable=SC2154
[ -f "$SHELL_COMMON/aliases.sh" ] && . "$SHELL_COMMON/aliases.sh"

# FZF integration based on shell type
if type fzf >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  if [ "$CURRENT_SHELL" = "zsh" ]; then
    # zsh-specific FZF integration (uses process substitution, zsh-only)
    # shellcheck disable=SC3001
    . <(fzf --zsh)
  else
    # bash-specific FZF integration
    if [ -f ~/.fzf.bash ]; then
      . ~/.fzf.bash
    elif [ -f /usr/share/doc/fzf/examples/key-bindings.bash ]; then
      . /usr/share/doc/fzf/examples/key-bindings.bash
    fi
  fi
fi

# Update checkers (tools and dotfiles)
[ -f "$SHELL_COMMON/updates/chezmoi.sh" ] && . "$SHELL_COMMON/updates/chezmoi.sh"
[ -f "$SHELL_COMMON/updates/mise.sh" ] && . "$SHELL_COMMON/updates/mise.sh"
[ -f "$SHELL_COMMON/updates/dotfiles.sh" ] && . "$SHELL_COMMON/updates/dotfiles.sh"

- 現在の方式：`precmd` で `date` を実行 → 結果をリテラルとして PROMPT に埋め込む → 何かが PROMPT をキャッシュ → 古い時刻のまま
- 修正方式：PROMPT 文字列に `$(date ...)` をリテラルで含め、`PROMPT_SUBST` に展開を任せる → キャッシュされても表示時に `$(date ...)` が再評価される
- `PROMPT_SUBST` はプロンプト**表示時**に `$()` や `$var` を展開するので、キャッシュを突き抜けて毎回最新の値を取得できる

toolUseResult.originalFile:
setopt PROMPT_SUBST

autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook

# Load shared helpers
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration: preexec starts timer ---
add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start

# --- Single precmd to capture $? before any other processing ---
__prompt_precmd() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Stop timer and compute duration
  __prompt_cmd_timer_stop

  # Gather git info
  __prompt_git_info

  # Build prompt
  __prompt_render "$exit_code"
}

add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_precmd

# --- Prompt renderer ---
__prompt_render() {
  local exit_code=$1

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir='%F{green}%B%~%b%f'
  local user
  if [ $UID -eq 0 ]; then
    user='%F{red}%B%n%b%f'
  else
    user='%F{cyan}%B%n%b%f'
  fi
  local host='%F{blue}%B%m%b%f'
  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon=$'\u2705'
  else
    status_icon=$'\u274c'" %F{red}${exit_code}%f"
  fi
  local current_time
  current_time=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')
  local timestamp="%F{blue}at ${current_time}%f"

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" %F{yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}%f"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}%F{yellow}@%f${host} ${status_icon} ${timestamp}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="%F{cyan}%B${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}%b%f"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}%f"
    fi

    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}%B(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})%b%f"
    fi

    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{cyan}[${ab}]%f"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
  else
    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
  fi

  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
__prompt_newline_precmd() {
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    print
  fi
}
add-zsh-hook precmd __prompt_newline_precmd

content.thinking:
The user is explaining that the original starship behavior was:
- When a prompt is first displayed, it shows the time at that point
- When a command is executed, the time shown on THAT prompt line updates to the command execution time

This is a feature where the timestamp on a prompt line reflects when the command was executed, not when the prompt was first rendered. This is similar to how some terminals/prompts work - they update the previous prompt's timestamp when a command starts.

In starship, the `[time]` module shows the current time when the prompt is rendered. But the key behavior the user is describing is: once you type a command and press Enter, the PREVIOUS prompt's time should update to reflect the actual execution time.


---

Ah, I see—the prompt initially displays with the render time, but when the command is actually executed, that same prompt line's timestamp updates to show when execution happened. This would require re-rendering the prompt when a command is submitted, which in zsh could be handled through preexec hooks or zle widgets.

But wait, that doesn't quite make sense either—once text is printed to the terminal, you can't go back and change it. Unless they mean the *next* prompt shows the current execution time, which is just standard behavior. Let me reconsider what they're describing: maybe the prompt updates dynamically while the user is typing, or perhaps there's a mechanism I'm not thinking of that allows updating previously-printed text.

Actually, I think I understand now—this sounds like a transient prompt feature where the prompt line itself gets redrawn when you press Enter. In zsh, you can use a `zle` widget to hook into the accept-line action, update the PROMPT variable with the current time, and call `zle reset-prompt` to refresh the display. So the sequence would be: the prompt appears with time T1, the user types their command, and when they hit Enter, the prompt rerenders with the updated time T2 before the command executes.

But looking at how starship actually works, it re-renders the prompt through `precmd` after you press Enter, which means the old prompt's timestamp stays frozen while the new prompt below it shows the new time. I'm wondering if starship has some other mechanism for updating the transient prompt specifically.

Actually, rereading the user's request more carefully—they mention this feature "existed before"—I think they might be asking for the timestamp to reflect when the command was *executed*, not when the prompt was initially displayed. With the current `PROMPT_SUBST` approach using `$(date ...)`, the time gets evaluated at prompt display time, so it shows when the prompt appeared, not when Enter was pressed. To show the execution time instead, I'd need to capture the timestamp at a different point in the lifecycle.

I'm considering using a `zle` widget that hooks into the accept-line action to update the prompt's time right before the command runs, which would be cleaner than using separate `preexec` and `precmd` hooks.

Still writing the widget implementation...

Actually, `zle reset-prompt` re-renders the current prompt without running precmd, so if the PROMPT contains a `$(date ...)` command substitution with PROMPT_SUBST enabled, it'll execute again and show the current time—exactly when Enter was pressed. The nice part is that other prompt elements like git info or exit codes stay frozen from the original render, while only the timestamp updates. Writing the zsh widget...

For bash, the situation's different since there's no `zle` equivalent—`PROMPT_COMMAND` already updates the time before each prompt appears, but capturing the exact moment Enter is pressed would require the DEBUG trap, which gets complicated. I'll stick with the zsh approach for now.

Before I override `accept-line`, I should check whether that'll interfere with other widgets like fzf's history selection.

Looking at the existing bindings, fzf-history-selection is bound to Ctrl+R and calls `zle reset-prompt` at the end, so it doesn't conflict. The Tab completion binding also doesn't touch `accept-line`. VSCode shell integration might be a concern since it could override my widget after loading, but it typically just wraps the prompt with escape sequences rather than replacing the widget entirely.

Now I'm ready to implement the zle widget in prompt.zsh. I need to verify that `zle reset-prompt` will actually re-evaluate the `$(date ...)` command in the prompt when PROMPT_SUBST is enabled—and yes, it should work since reset-prompt re-displays the prompt and triggers parameter expansion.

setopt PROMPT_SUBST

autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook

# Load shared helpers
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration: preexec starts timer ---
add-zsh-hook preexec __prompt_cmd_timer_start

# --- Single precmd to capture $? before any other processing ---
__prompt_precmd() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Stop timer and compute duration
  __prompt_cmd_timer_stop

  # Gather git info

  # Build prompt

  fi
  local host='%F{blue}%B%m%b%f'

  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then

  fi

  local timestamp='%F{blue}at $(date "+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")%f'

  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" %F{yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}%f"
  fi

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="%F{cyan}%B${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}%b%f"

    fi

    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{cyan}[${ab}]%f"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted%f"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} %F{red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked%f"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="%F{green}%B>%b%f "
  else
    mark="%F{red}%B>%b%f "
  fi

  PROMPT="${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
__prompt_newline_precmd() {
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    print
  fi
}

content.text:
bash 側は時刻表示はありますが、zsh で実装した「Enter 押下時に更新」の仕組みはありません。

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **zsh** は `zle` (Zsh Line Editor) があるので `accept-line` ウィジェットをオーバーライドして Enter 押下時にプロンプトを再描画できる
- **bash** には `zle` に相当する仕組みがない。`PROMPT_COMMAND` はプロンプト表示前に実行されるが、Enter 押下時にプロンプトを書き換える標準的な方法がない
- bash では `\D{format}` を PS1 に直接入れるのが最も素直。プロンプト表示時の時刻になるが、bash の制約上これがベスト
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

bash では Enter 押下時の更新はできないため、`\D{...}` を使ったプロンプト表示時の時刻表示に留めるのが妥当です。現在の `$(date ...)` を `\D{...}` に戻して subprocess を減らしておきます。

#!/bin/bash
# Bash-specific prompt implementation

# Variables PROMPT_GIT_* and PROMPT_CMD_DURATION are set by sourced helpers
# shellcheck disable=SC2154

# shellcheck source=git_info.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/git_info.sh"
# shellcheck source=cmd_duration.sh
[ -f "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh" ] && . "$HOME/.shell_common/prompt/cmd_duration.sh"

# --- Command duration via DEBUG trap ---
# Only set if no existing DEBUG trap to avoid conflicts
if [ -z "$(trap -p DEBUG)" ]; then
  trap '__prompt_cmd_timer_start' DEBUG
  _PROMPT_HAS_DURATION=1
fi

# --- Color helpers for bash (non-printing escape wrappers) ---
_c_reset='\[\033[0m\]'
_c_bold='\[\033[1m\]'
_c_green='\[\033[32m\]'
_c_red='\[\033[31m\]'
_c_cyan='\[\033[36m\]'
_c_blue='\[\033[34m\]'
_c_yellow='\[\033[33m\]'
_c_bold_green='\[\033[1;32m\]'
_c_bold_red='\[\033[1;31m\]'
_c_bold_cyan='\[\033[1;36m\]'
_c_bold_blue='\[\033[1;34m\]'

# --- Main prompt builder ---
__prompt_bash_build() {
  local exit_code=$?

  # Run shared helpers
  __prompt_git_info
  if [ "$_PROMPT_HAS_DURATION" = "1" ]; then
    __prompt_cmd_timer_stop
  fi

  # Line 1: directory user@host status [duration]
  local dir="${_c_bold_green}\w${_c_reset}"
  local user
  if [ "$(id -u)" -eq 0 ]; then
    user="${_c_bold_red}\u${_c_reset}"
  else
    user="${_c_bold_cyan}\u${_c_reset}"
  fi
  local host="${_c_bold_blue}\h${_c_reset}"

  local status_icon
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    status_icon='✅'
  else
    status_icon='❌'" ${_c_red}${exit_code}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local current_time
  current_time=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')
  local timestamp="${_c_blue}at ${current_time}${_c_reset}"

  local duration=""
  if [ -n "$PROMPT_CMD_DURATION" ]; then
    duration=" ${_c_yellow}took ${PROMPT_CMD_DURATION}${_c_reset}"
  fi

  local line1="${dir} ${user}${_c_yellow}@${_c_reset}${host} ${status_icon} ${timestamp}${duration}"

  # Line 2: git info (only in git repos)
  local line2=""
  if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_ACTIVE" = "1" ]; then
    local git_parts="${_c_bold_cyan}${PROMPT_GIT_BRANCH}${_c_reset}"
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_blue}→ ${PROMPT_GIT_REMOTE}${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # State (merge, rebase, etc.)
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_STATE" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_bold_red}(${PROMPT_GIT_STATE})${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Ahead/behind
    local ab=""
    if [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ] && [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇕⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD" ]; then
      ab="⇡${PROMPT_GIT_AHEAD}"
    elif [ -n "$PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND" ]; then
      ab="⇣${PROMPT_GIT_BEHIND}"
    fi
    if [ -n "$ab" ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_cyan}[${ab}]${_c_reset}"
    fi

    # Clean indicator
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -eq 0 ] && \
       [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -eq 0 ] && [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -eq 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ✨"
    fi

    # File status counts
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_STAGED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_green}+${PROMPT_GIT_STAGED} staged${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_yellow}!${PROMPT_GIT_MODIFIED} modified${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_DELETED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}✘${PROMPT_GIT_DELETED} deleted${_c_reset}"
    fi
    if [ "$PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED" -gt 0 ]; then
      git_parts="${git_parts} ${_c_red}?${PROMPT_GIT_UNTRACKED} untracked${_c_reset}"
    fi

    line2=$'\n'"${git_parts}"
  fi

  # Line 3: prompt character
  local mark
  if [ "$exit_code" -eq 0 ]; then
    mark="${_c_bold_green}>${_c_reset} "
  else
    mark="${_c_bold_red}>${_c_reset} "
  fi

  # Add newline before prompt (except first prompt)
  local newline=""
  if [ -z "$_PROMPT_FIRST" ]; then
    _PROMPT_FIRST=1
  else
    newline=$'\n'
  fi

  PS1="${newline}${line1}${line2}"$'\n'"${mark}"
}

# Append to PROMPT_COMMAND without overwriting existing entries
if [ -n "$PROMPT_COMMAND" ]; then
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build;${PROMPT_COMMAND}"
else
  PROMPT_COMMAND="__prompt_bash_build"
fi
